Valign="top"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial">SS.6.W.4.3</span></td><td width="75%"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial">Recognize the political and cultural achievements of the Mauryan and Gupta empires.</span><table align="center" border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse;width:100%;font-family: Arial;font-size: 9.0pt;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bordercolor="#000000"> <tr colpsan="2" style="width:100%;font-family: Arial"><td style="width:100%;text-align:center;font-weight:bold;">Related Access Point(s)</td></tr> <tr>      <td> SS.6.W.4.AP.3<br>Identify the political and cultural achievements of the Mauryan and Gupta empires.<br /><i><u>Date Adopted or Revised</u></i>: 05/23<br /></td>    </tr> </table></td></tr></table>     </td></tr></table><table align="center" width="100%" border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bordercolor="#000000"><tr><td width="25%" align="center" Valign="top"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial">SS.6.W.4.4</span></td><td width="75%"><span style="font-size: 9.0pt; font-family: Arial">Explain the teachings of Buddha, the importance of Asoka, and how Buddhism spread in India, Ceylon, and other parts of Asia.</span><table align="center" border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse;width:100%;font-family: Arial;font-size: 9.0pt;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bordercolor="#000000"> <tr colpsan="2" style="width:100%;font-family: Arial"><td style="width:100%;text-align:center;font-weight:bold;">Related Access Point(s)</td></tr> <tr>      <td> SS.6.W.4.AP.4<br>Identify the teachings of Buddha and trace how Buddhism spread in India, Ceylon, and other parts of Asia.<br /><i><u>Date Adopted or Revised</u></i>: 05/23<br /></td>    </tr> </table></td></tr></table>     </td></tr></table><table align="center" width="100%" border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bordercolor="#000000"><tr><td width="25%" align="center" Valign="to